{Syntax:}\par is_orthogonal(Line1, Line2) or is_orthogonal(Circle1, Circle2\par
\par Tests whether or not two lines or two circles are orthogonal (perpendicular). In the case of two circles, tests whether or not the tangent lines at a point of intersection are orthogonal. Returns 1 if they are and 0 otherwise.\par
{\par Example:}\par is_orthogonal(line(y=x),line(y=-x)) returns 1.\par }